<% content_for :title, "Booking Calendar — Help" %>

<div class="flex gap-8 lg:gap-12">
  <aside class="hidden lg:block w-52 flex-shrink-0">
    <%= render "sidebar" %>
  </aside>

  <article class="min-w-0 flex-1">
    <%= render BreadcrumbComponent.new(items: [
      { label: "Help", path: help_path },
      { label: "Booking Calendar", path: nil }
    ]) %>

    <h1 class="mt-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-stone-900">Booking Calendar</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-stone-500">Understand slot statuses and how to select the hours you want.</p>

    <div class="mt-8 space-y-8 text-stone-700">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Slot Colors</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          The home page shows a calendar of all studio time. Each block represents one hour and is
          color-coded so you can see availability at a glance:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 rounded-xl border border-stone-200 bg-white p-5">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="mt-0.5 inline-block h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-red-500"></span>
            <div>
              <strong>Open</strong> — available to book. Click to select.
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="mt-0.5 inline-block h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-yellow-400"></span>
            <div>
              <strong>Held</strong> — another customer is currently checking out. The hold lasts only
              a couple of minutes; the slot may become available again if they don't complete payment.
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="mt-0.5 inline-block h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-blue-500"></span>
            <div>
              <strong>Reserved</strong> — already booked and paid for. Not available.
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="mt-0.5 inline-block h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-stone-400"></span>
            <div>
              <strong>Cancelled</strong> — this slot has been removed from the schedule.
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4">
          The calendar updates in real time. If a slot becomes available or gets taken while you're
          browsing, your view updates automatically without requiring a page refresh.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Selecting Multiple Hours</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-3">
          <p>
            To book a single hour, click that slot. To book multiple consecutive hours, click the
            <strong>first</strong> slot you want, then click the <strong>last</strong> slot. All open
            slots between them are selected automatically, and the running total updates as you select.
          </p>
          <p>
            You can only select consecutive open slots. If a held or reserved slot falls anywhere in
            the middle of your desired range, you'll need to work around it by choosing different hours.
          </p>
          <p>
            To deselect, click a selected slot again, or start a fresh selection by clicking a different
            starting slot.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Proceeding to Checkout</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-3">
          <p>
            Once you have selected your slots, click <strong>Continue to Checkout</strong>. You must
            be signed in — if you aren't, you'll be prompted to sign in first.
          </p>
          <p>
            See <strong><%= link_to "Checkout & Payment", help_checkout_path, class: "underline hover:text-stone-900" %></strong>
            for what happens next.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">No Slots Available?</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-3">
          <p>
            If the calendar is empty — no open slots in the next 30 days — you'll see a
            <strong>Join Waitlist</strong> button instead. Click it and you'll receive an email
            the moment new slots are added or a booking is cancelled. You can leave the waitlist at
            any time using the button on the same page.
          </p>
          <p>
            See <%= link_to "Waitlist", help_waitlist_path, class: "underline hover:text-stone-900" %> for more details.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</div>
